This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Science sub-category of Network and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) as it deals with improving the scheduling decisions in Multipath TCP (MPTCP) by incorporating local queue buffer occupancy information. It could also belong to the sub-category of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) as MPTCP is a security-critical protocol. Additionally, it involves system-level design and optimization, which could place it in the sub-categories of Systems and Control (cs.SY) and Information Theory (cs.IT). Finally, it deals with improving the efficiency of resource utilization, which could place it in the sub-category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC).
